<h1>Mums (Chrysanthemum)</h1>

<p>
Mums, or chrysanthemums, are popular autumn-blooming flowers known for their dense, colorful flower heads and long-lasting blooms.
</p>

<h2>Description</h2>

<p>
Chrysanthemums produce layered blooms in many forms including daisy-like, pompon, spider, and decorative shapes.
They appear in a wide range of colors such as yellow, white, red, purple, and bronze.
</p>

<p>
They are widely used in gardens, floral arrangements, and seasonal displays.
</p>

<h2>Taxonomy</h2>

<p>
Mums belong to the genus <strong>Chrysanthemum</strong> in the family <strong>Asteraceae</strong>.
They are native to Asia and northeastern Europe.
</p>

